你得以我为傲 我是个很不错的成员
You'd have been proud of me.I was a real team player.

154
00:09:23,013 --> 00:09:24,731
你真坦白 Danny
Your round,Danny.

155
00:09:30,093 --> 00:09:34,211
你好 我想知道上一场是谁赢了?
Hello.I was wondering if you could tell me what won the last race?

156
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:37,052
随便哪个比赛
Anywhere.

157
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:42,088
很好 非常感谢
That's excellent.Thank you.

158
00:09:46,933 --> 00:09:49,163
我听说你被某个女人拒绝了?
I heard you got blanked by some bird at the hotel.

159
00:09:49,253 --> 00:09:53,326
我没有被拒绝好不好?她是个同性恋
I did not get blanked,okay?She's a lesbian.

160
00:09:53,413 --> 00:09:54,562
是的 没错
Right.

161
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:58,928
早些时候 有个家伙来这儿找你
Had some bloke in here earlier,looking for you.

162
00:09:59,373 --> 00:10:00,362
谁?
What bloke?

163
00:10:00,453 --> 00:10:04,685
没留名字 不过他好象留了电话号码
He didn't leave his name,but he left his number here somewhere.

164
00:10:14,373 --> 00:10:16,762
看上去有点道理啊 就是你说的
It seems it's true,what you say.

165
00:10:17,253 --> 00:10:19,005
笨蛋是发不了财的
About a fool and his money.

166
00:10:19,653 --> 00:10:21,928
这上面说有个家伙
There's a chap in here.

167
00:10:26,053 --> 00:10:29,523
他被骗 据说是他竟然以为 自己买到了"伦敦眼"
He was apparently conned into believing he was buying the London Eye.

168
00:10:26,053 --> 00:10:29,523
{\an8}伦敦眼:世界最大的观景摩天轮

169
00:10:29,613 --> 00:10:30,602
是吗?
Really?

170
00:10:30,693 --> 00:10:33,491
显然他太想得到它了
Apparently turned up to take possession.

171
00:10:33,573 --> 00:10:36,610
- 他到底在想什么? - 谁知道呢
- What was he thinking of? - I can't imagine.

172
00:10:39,053 --> 00:10:40,042
谢谢!
Thank you.

173
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:43,091
问题是 有些人不该拥有那么多钱
Problem is,some people don't deserve money.

174
00:10:43,173 --> 00:10:44,845
象我们这样的人 稍有点钱
When chaps like us earn a few bob...

175
00:10:46,053 --> 00:10:47,725
就被说成中饱私囊
they call us fat cats.

176
00:10:48,453 --> 00:10:51,684
象我 即使有人中了彩票 我也不会嫉妒的
I mean,I don't moan when one of the plebs wins the lottery,do I?

177
00:10:51,773 --> 00:10:53,764
我就没你那么大度了
I could hardly put it better myself.

178
00:10:53,853 --> 00:10:56,731
当然 希望他不会成为我的邻居
Providing he doesn't move in next to me,of course.

179
00:11:01,613 --> 00:11:03,171
Margo's girl
Margo's Girl.

180
00:11:04,893 --> 00:11:05,928
你说什么?
I'm sorry?

181
00:11:06,013 --> 00:11:09,562
你刚刚问我马的名字 是Margo's Girl 下午1点的
That horse you asked me about,Margo's Girl,1:00 p.m.

182
00:11:09,693 --> 00:11:11,206
突然间想起来了
It just came back to me.

183
00:11:11,293 --> 00:11:12,772
哪场比赛 你知道吗?
Where was it running,do you know?

184
00:11:12,853 --> 00:11:14,684
我不清楚
I have no idea.

185
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:17,007
我想知道它有没有赢?
I wonder if it won?

186
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:19,288
想知道结果 那很简单
It's easy enough to find out.

187
00:11:19,373 --> 00:11:22,809
Paul 有匹马叫Margo's Girl 参加今天的某场比赛
Paul,there was a horse running today,Margo's Girl.

188
00:11:22,893 --> 00:11:25,805
可以替我看看结果如何吗?
Could you see how it did for me,there's a good chap.

189
00:11:26,493 --> 00:11:29,246
- 要是真赢了 你就该后悔了 - 我不沾赌的
- You'll be sick if it won. - I never gamble.

190
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:31,642
偶尔的一两次刺激 无伤大雅
There's nothing wrong with an occasional flutter.

191
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,928
我对赛马是一窍不通
I don't know one end of the horse from the other.

192
00:11:34,013 --> 00:11:35,924
那可是"运动之王" 老伙计
It's the sport of kings,old chap.

193
00:11:36,013 --> 00:11:38,208
看着你的马跑向Cheltenham的山顶
You haven't lived till you've seen your horse...

194
00:11:38,293 --> 00:11:40,204
你才会觉得生活是如此有意义
running up that hill at Cheltenham.

195
00:11:40,293 --> 00:11:42,409
我会记得你说的
I'll have to take your word for it.

196
00:11:45,013 --> 00:11:47,004
Margo's Girl赢了 先生
Margo's Girl won,sir.

197
00:11:49,813 --> 00:11:51,724
- 赔率? - 1赔12
- Price? - 12-to-1.

198
00:11:53,013 --> 00:11:54,332
真不错
Good Lord.

199
00:11:57,053 --> 00:12:01,808
你的这个故友之子 他到底是做什么的?
This nephew of yours,what does he do exactly?

200
00:12:01,893 --> 00:12:05,249
说实话 我也不清楚 只知道是关于马的
Tell you the truth,I'm not sure.Just something to do with horses.

201
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,688
我很希望有机会再见见他
I'd very much like to meet him again.

202
00:12:08,453 --> 00:12:11,763
行啊 我想没问题
Well,I'm sure that can be arranged.

203
00:12:42,173 --> 00:12:44,004
你就是Danny
You must be Danny.

204
00:12:44,093 --> 00:12:47,085
- 我不确信你会来 - 是的 我很好奇
- Wasn't sure you'd come. - Well,I was curious.

205
00:12:48,413 --> 00:12:52,042
听着 伙计 我没时间 你是谁 找我干什么?
Listen,mate,I ain't got all day,so who are you and what do you want?

206
00:12:52,133 --> 00:12:54,044
我叫Ray Fordham
The name's Ray Fordham.

207
00:12:55,533 --> 00:12:58,366
你有他们说的那么厉害吗 Danny?
Are you as good as they say you are,Danny?

208
00:13:00,493 --> 00:13:02,131
你到底是谁?警察?
What are you then?Cop?

209
00:13:03,053 --> 00:13:04,884
我看上去象警察吗?
Do I look like a cop?

210
00:13:04,973 --> 00:13:07,328
警察长什么样的都有 不是嘛?
Well,they come in all shapes and sizes,don't they?

211
00:13:07,413 --> 00:13:09,244
我也是个骗子 和你一样
I'm a grifter,just like you.

212
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:12,086
是吗?我怎么从来没听说过?
Are you?How come I never heard of you then?

213
00:13:12,173 --> 00:13:14,607
你听过苏格兰的Ray?
You have.Scottish Ray?

214
00:13:14,693 --> 00:13:17,287
你就是苏格兰的Ray?你又不是苏格兰人
You're Scottish Ray?But you ain't even Scottish.

215
00:13:17,373 --> 00:13:20,206
这个名字是出自我做的第一个大案
The name came from my first big con.

216
00:13:20,293 --> 00:13:22,966
我用爱丁堡城堡的项目 骗了5万定金
I took a 50,000 down payment on Edinburgh Castle.

217
00:13:23,053 --> 00:13:25,089
是的 我听说过
Yeah,I've heard about that.

218
00:13:25,173 --> 00:13:28,051
是在94年?
'94,weren't it?

219
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,851
95年
'95.

220
00:13:29,973 --> 00:13:32,851
又靠它的室内装饰项目 骗了2万
I took another 20,000 for putting in double-glazing.

221
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,605
你是不是很喜欢美国佬?
Don't you just love the Yanks?

222
00:13:34,693 --> 00:13:37,412
是啊 他们天生爱冒险
Yes,they've got romance in their soul.

223
00:13:37,613 --> 00:13:40,332
好的 很高兴认识你 Ray
All right,I'm glad to meet you,Ray.

224
00:13:40,413 --> 00:13:41,732
我也是
Likewise.

225
00:13:42,173 --> 00:13:43,731
我可以做什么 伙计?
So what can I do for you,mate?

226
00:13:43,813 --> 00:13:45,326
我正在组个新队伍
I'm putting a new crew together.

227
00:13:45,413 --> 00:13:47,324
是吗?不错 我认识不少人
Yeah?Well,I know some people.

228
00:13:47,413 --> 00:13:50,291
我不要其他人 Danny 我要你
I don't want people,Danny.I want you.

229
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,405
好的 我想我们已经做得够多了 足够让他相信我们了
Well,I think we've hooked him in enough to give him a convincer.

230
00:13:57,493 --> 00:13:59,609
Ash 你找到的地方如何?
Ash,what about this place you've found?

231
00:13:59,693 --> 00:14:01,092
还行 需要再做些装修
Well,it has to be a build.

232
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:03,403
可以 弄得象样点 需要多久?
Okay,but let's make it good.How long?

233
00:14:03,493 --> 00:14:05,643
几天吧 还要再找点帮手
Couple of days,if I can get enough bodies.

234
00:14:05,733 --> 00:14:07,166
没问题 就这么做
Yeah,do it.

235
00:14:14,573 --> 00:14:17,451
你半小时前就该来的
You should have been here half an hour ago.

236
00:14:18,413 --> 00:14:19,562
抱歉
Sorry.

237
00:14:20,493 --> 00:14:24,327
好的 后天Albert会安排 让他和Danny见一面
Right,Albert will set up the meet with Danny for the day after tomorrow.

238
00:14:24,413 --> 00:14:26,404
- 你得准备好 - 我会的
- You have to be ready by then. - I will be.

239
00:14:26,493 --> 00:14:30,372
Stacie 和Ash算下支出费用 后天你和Danny一起去
Stacie,work out the costs with Ash,then double up with Danny later on.

240
00:14:31,693 --> 00:14:33,012
有问题吗?
Questions?

241
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:35,651
好的 开始行动
Okay,let's do it.

242
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:46,807
你有问题?
Problem?

243
00:14:48,933 --> 00:14:50,127
没有
No.

244
00:14:57,293 --> 00:15:00,842
我的朋友告诉我 你可以找到任何人
A friend of mine down here tells me you can find anyone.

245
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:04,050
只要你找的人还在伦敦 我就能找到他
If who you're looking for is in London,I can find them.

246
00:15:04,293 --> 00:15:06,363
我要付多少钱?
How much is that going to cost me?

247
00:15:06,653 --> 00:15:07,927
看你找谁...
Depends who it is...

248
00:15:08,013 --> 00:15:10,129
找到之后打算怎么处置
and what you're going to do when you find them.

249
00:15:10,213 --> 00:15:13,011
2个骗子 一个黑人 一个白人
Two con men,one black,one white.

250
00:15:16,053 --> 00:15:17,532
我要杀了他们
I'm gonna kill them.

251
00:15:18,213 --> 00:15:19,328
进展如何?
How's it going?

252
00:15:19,413 --> 00:15:22,689
装饰很容易 不过我们需要搬些东西进来
Decoration's easy enough,but we need to start getting the hardware in.

253
00:15:22,773 --> 00:15:23,762
什么东西?
What's the setup?

254
00:15:23,853 --> 00:15:25,764
一些器材 适合那种半英里左右赛程的比赛
Five or six furlong races are the best bet.

255
00:15:25,853 --> 00:15:28,492
这样 比赛会在1分钟或1分半钟内结束
Means the race is over in a minute to a minute-and-a-half.

256
00:15:28,573 --> 00:15:32,486
- 很好 东西都准备好了吗? - 是的 该有的都有了
- Good.You've got everything you need? - Yeah.You'll know when I haven't.

257
00:15:32,893 --> 00:15:34,611
嘿 小心点 这可是问Teddy借来的
Steady with those.Teddy wants them back.

258
00:16:09,373 --> 00:16:11,284
James 见到你真高兴
James,what a lovely surprise.

259
00:16:11,373 --> 00:16:14,570
这是Peter和他的朋友 Yvonne
This is Peter,and his young friend,Yvonne.

260
00:16:15,293 --> 00:16:19,206
来吧 我给你们拿些饮料 Anthony在大厅
Come in,I'll fix you some drinks.Anthony's in the lounge.

261
00:16:21,693 --> 00:16:24,161
- James 欢迎啊 - 谢谢!
- James,welcome. - Thank you.

262
00:16:25,093 --> 00:16:27,607
- Peter 很高兴又见到你了 - 你好!
- Peter,nice to see you again. - Sir.

263
00:16:28,653 --> 00:16:32,009
这位美女是....?
And who is this vision of beauty?

264
00:16:33,133 --> 00:16:34,691
这是Yvonne
This is Yvonne.

265
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:46,127
认识你是我的荣幸 亲爱的
I'm delighted to make your acquaintance,my dear.

266
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:47,646
Anthony先生 您好
Sir Anthony.

267
00:16:49,053 --> 00:16:51,521
不介意我借用一下这个年轻人吧?
Do you mind if I steal this young man?

268
00:16:51,813 --> 00:16:53,212
当然不
Be my guest.

269
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:58,527
James告诉我 你很喜欢打赌
James tells me you're a betting man.

270
00:16:58,653 --> 00:17:00,006
不完全是 先生
Not really,sir.

271
00:17:00,093 --> 00:17:03,847
装聋作哑?来喝些东西 放松一下吧
Playing dumb?Lets see if a few drinks will loosen you up.

272
00:17:06,573 --> 00:17:08,165
正是我想看到的
That's what I like to see.

273
00:17:08,253 --> 00:17:11,051
鱼儿正在努力的自投罗网
A mark who does all the hard work himself.

274
00:17:12,453 --> 00:17:16,685
好的 把电视接收器放在这里 以便我们实时接收比赛过程
Okay.We get the TV feed in here showing us the live race.

275
00:17:16,773 --> 00:17:19,128
很明显 我们没办法控制比赛 他们是合法的
Obviously we can't fix the races,they're legit.

276
00:17:19,213 --> 00:17:22,444
但是这个小家伙 可以接收到比赛前所有的图象
But this little baby holds up the pictures until the end of the race.

277
00:17:22,533 --> 00:17:24,649
我们一知道谁获胜 就马上通知你
When we've got a winner,we'll give it to you.

278
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:26,485
在我们把图象信号传输到前厅之前
You've got two minutes to put a bet on...

279
00:17:26,573 --> 00:17:28,484
你有2分钟时间下注
before we start feeding it through the front.

280
00:17:28,573 --> 00:17:31,406
就所有人而言 他们是在看实况转播
As far as anyone is concerned,they're watching the race live.

281
00:17:31,493 --> 00:17:32,642
2分钟时间并不长
Two minutes isn't very long.

282
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:36,089
再慢一点 我们的鱼儿就会有察觉了
You slow up the pictures any more,our man might smell a rat.

283
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,086
那也是逼不得已
It'll have to do.

284
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:40,483
好的主要区域已经布置好了
Right.The main area is fully functioning.

285
00:17:40,573 --> 00:17:42,882
我从街灯上接了条线 作为我们的电力供应
I've tapped into a street light for electricity...

286
00:17:42,973 --> 00:17:44,804
改了厕所的水流管道
re-routed mains water for the toilets.

287
00:17:44,893 --> 00:17:46,804
只要他不踢墙....
As long as he doesn't kick the walls...

288
00:17:46,893 --> 00:17:48,929
一切足够维持到任务结束
they should stay up long enough for the job.

289
00:17:49,013 --> 00:17:50,241
完美的工作!
It's a work of art.

290
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:53,006
没错 我还找了20个小混混来做托
Yeah.I've got 20 grifters coming in as punters.

291
00:17:53,093 --> 00:17:56,290
他们一来 这里就成"狼窝"了
When they're here,it will be the doggie's whatsits.

292
00:17:56,693 --> 00:17:59,366
- 很好 明天我们就能开始 - 好的
- Okay,then we can start tomorrow. - Yeah.

293
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:02,843
我想说的是 你可以给我一些小道消息嘛
All I'm asking is that you throw the odd tip my way.

294
00:18:02,933 --> 00:18:04,525
那超出了我的职权范围
It's more than my job's worth.

295
00:18:04,613 --> 00:18:05,762
你告诉了James
You did it for James.

296
00:18:05,853 --> 00:18:09,004
是的 但是他实质上就和家人一样 我的意思是 他能为我做任何事
Yeah,but he's virtually family.I mean,he'd do anything for me.

297
00:18:09,093 --> 00:18:12,290
除了应有的尊重 先生 我几乎不了解你 是吧?
With all due respect,sir,I hardly even know you,do I?

298
00:18:12,373 --> 00:18:14,125
James会为我担保的
James will vouch for me.

299
00:18:14,253 --> 00:18:15,686
是吗?
Will he,now?

300
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:19,322
您是做什么?各种比赛 是吗?
So what are you?A racing man,are you?

301
00:18:19,413 --> 00:18:22,291
我想 我该属于那种狂热的爱好者
I think I'm what you'd call an enthusiastic amateur.

302
00:18:23,973 --> 00:18:28,842
听着 我要告诉你的事 不能让其他人知道
Listen,what I'm about to tell you mustn't go any further.

303
00:18:29,093 --> 00:18:30,765
我保证!
You have my word.

304
00:18:31,573 --> 00:18:33,723
我为syndicate工作
I work for a syndicate.

305
00:18:35,093 --> 00:18:36,492
我们买比赛用的马
We buy racehorses.

306
00:18:36,573 --> 00:18:38,848
我知道 你们有内部消息
I knew it.You've got inside knowledge.

307
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:40,252
有时候还不止这些
It's slightly more than that.

308
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:45,123
去年 我的东家和其他三家财团合作
Last year the company that I work for teamed up with three other syndicates.

309
00:18:45,213 --> 00:18:48,922
去年 在Kempton 我们发现
Then at Kempton last year,we realized that between them...

310
00:18:49,373 --> 00:18:52,649
他们拥有某一比赛中所有的马
they owned all the runners in a single race.

311
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:53,768
真的?
Really?

312
00:18:53,853 --> 00:18:57,323
这样 他们所需要做的就是
From there it's just a short step to being able to determine...

313
00:18:57,413 --> 00:19:00,291
决定哪一场次是哪匹马赢
which horses are going to win certain races.

314
00:19:00,693 --> 00:19:01,842
你是说 暗箱操作?
You mean,fix them?

315
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:05,289
我没说是暗箱操作 我只是说 他们在比赛前就知道
I'm not saying fix them.I'm just saying they know who's going to win...

316
00:19:05,373 --> 00:19:07,045
哪匹马会赢
before they start.

317
00:19:07,213 --> 00:19:09,363
而你 可以知道获胜者的名字?
And you can get the names of the winning horses?

318
00:19:09,453 --> 00:19:12,365
我?不 我只是个打工的
Me?No.I'm much too far down the food chain.

319
00:19:12,453 --> 00:19:14,921
但是 你告诉过James马的名字
But the horse you told James about.

320
